{
  "texts": [
    "They did not focus on generating natural, human-like iCRs in response to partial sentences.",
    "Using a subset of their SLUICE corpus (Addlesee and Damonte, 2023a), we elicited 12 CRs from annotators for 250 interrupted questions.",
    "This new corpus SLUICE-CR, therefore, contains a total of 3,000 human CRs (Addlesee, 2024).",
    "All CRs within SLUICE-CR are intended to elicit how the interlocutor would have gone on to complete their turn.",
    "Example (E) in Table 1 illustrates this."
  ]
}